Nameless  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unaginatakuroshio.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Naginata Kuroshio</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.rose-hulman.edu/~acuffnd/Reference/icon1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master of The Elements</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#333333>(12/18/00 4:14:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=46.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Has this  happened to anyone else?</span><hr size=1> This has only happened to me once, but the opinion that we are nothing more than wizzies with pets is not uncommon, even at higher levels, when the difference is most pronounced.  The one time this happened to me, I just told the group, in groupsay, that the following needed to happen:<br>
(for reference, the group was 1 warrior, 1 cleric, 1 magician, 1 druid, 1 ranger, 1 wizzie)<br>
<br>
Ok, from now on, [druid] needs to do the damage shields, and pick some extra healing on [warrior], since I can't feed [cleric] anymore.  Also, [Ranger], you'll probably need to start healing yourself, and no more arrows for pulling.  Oh, and [wizard], I need you to keep an eye on my pet.  In fact, see if you can find an enchanter to sit with us and keep him hasted.<br>
<br>
The response to this was the ranger and warrior in groupsay, and the cleric in tells, all saying, more or less, &quot;what the hell are you doing?&quot;, and the wizard saying &quot;just kill the pet, he isn't helping anyway&quot;, to which the ranger, a friend of mine, responded &quot;[wizard], are you %&amp;$^ing crazy? That thing is outdamaging ME!&quot;  Strangely enough, 30 minutes later, the wizard was gone, and we had picked up another mage.  Go figure <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><table width="100%" border="0">
