<br>
That being said... there is merit to just being a nuke machine every once in a while <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
For example, if your mobs drop very quickly anyway maybe that DS really isn't worth it when another nuke would do more damage. Also true with multiple taunting classes or (very nice) Rogue and Warrior ping pong going on. It is simply not worth the mana to DS two people when neither take a lot of hits.<br>
<br>
Now on Mod rods... I haven't used the spell, but following similar reasoning as above, would the mana spent on the mod rod enable another nuke? Would the nuke save more damage from the tank than the cleric can heal with the mana you give with a mod rod?<br>
(killing mob faster = less hits on tank = less for cleric to heal) <br>
<br>
And arrows for pulling? Burst of fire works good in a pinch and takes a trivial amount of mana (probably recovered by the time the ranger can make it back to camp anyway) the only plus being our arrows are free (although at the levels you mentioned I sell 3or 4 dmg 150 rng arrows to high lvl rangers like they are water, even at 3-4x my cost <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
What's my point in all of this? Try not to get too offended by someone who's tactics are from a different mind set <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Could be they do not speak much English, and &quot;Mage needs to nuke more&quot; is all they could translate <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Of course, could be they were the typical know it all kid assuming since he grouped with a nuke nuke nuke OOM type mage and it worked before that it's the only way to be <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I've done both methods at different times. Both can be fun and most of the time both will work. Only the spawn timing, and your group's timing make the difference on which you can use <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I like being able to provide SOMETHING for everyone in the group. So a majority of the time I summon like crazy during down times and do not do too much other than &quot;/pet attack&quot; and Bolt/Shock then med through a normal fight. When ever I am in this mode, I like to occasionally nuke three times and watch the melee types whine about only getting in two hits, or the wizzy whine about his wasted third DD <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Just as a reminder to the group that I can burn with the best of 'em.<br>
<br>
On very rare occasions I'll send good old Vobartik to beat the crap out of something SOLO while the group fights a different mob. It's stupid since I loose a safety margin of the extra back up mana, but I have NEVER been told maybe I should nuke more <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Most of the time I get &quot;Why do you group? You just soloed the same MOB we've GROUPED to fight?!?&quot;.<br>
<br>
Oh, yeah, I almost forgot...<br>
<br>
I usually leave the game/camp with my summons memmed so next time I log on I can summon all the stuff I'll be giving away in a group setting/or just to be friendly (us blind folk love coldstones). This used to work great and gave me more mana in a group setting since I recovered that mana loss while looking for a group or hunting spot. Now with the new linkdeath=loss of all summoned stuff it's not so great, but still works most of the time. Most of the time now I only do food/water/band aids/stones since I know I'll need them anyway.<br>
<br>
And in final closing notes...<br>
<br>
1. In well balanced groups what exact tactics you use both ways work <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
2. You're all totally correct. Sometimes know it all punk kids trying to tell you how to play when they have no clue what else you're doing (I rarely summon anything for wizzies) need to be put in their place <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
3. I spent entirely too long talking about something that really boils down to playing styles <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
